{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775880282205,"sessionID":"ses_2854e7c0bffe5w0RmAD0fpq7ai","part":{"id":"prt_d7ab6a03a001eJweJTJxnaGuzc","messageID":"msg_d7ab65ecf001tRWpduZm5p8Axc","sessionID":"ses_2854e7c0bffe5w0RmAD0fpq7ai","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-6112b4b9dbef44aaaa5db302cb699be5","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AgentCube Python SDK\n\nPython client library (`agentcube-sdk`) for creating Code Interpreter sessions via the Workload Manager (control plane) and executing code/files via the Router (data plane), plus invoking AgentRuntime workloads through the Router.\n\n## Features\n\n- **Code Interpreter**: Create sessions, execute commands, run Python code, manage files\n- **Agent Runtime**: Bootstrap sessions, invoke agents with custom payloads\n- **HTTP Clients**: Connection pooling, configurable timeouts, automatic retries\n- **Authentication**: Support for Bearer tokens and Kubernetes service account tokens\n- **Context Managers**: Automatic session cleanup with `with` statements\n\n## Installation\n\n```bash\npip install agentcube-sdk\n```\n\n## Quick Start\n\n### Code Interpreter\n\n```python\nfrom agentcube import CodeInterpreterClient\n\n# Create a new session\nclient = CodeInterpreterClient(\n    name=\"my-interpreter\",\n    namespace=\"default\",\n    router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n    workload_manager_url=\"http://workload-manager:8080\",\n)\n\n# Execute a command\noutput = client.execute_command(\"ls -la\")\nprint(output)\n\n# Run Python code\nresult = client.run_code(\"python\", \"print('Hello, World!')\")\nprint(result)\n\n# Write a file\nclient.write_file(\"Hello, World!\", \"/tmp/hello.txt\")\n\n# Upload a file\nclient.upload_file(\"./local.txt\", \"/tmp/remote.txt\")\n\n# Download a file\nclient.download_file(\"/tmp/remote.txt\", \"./downloaded.txt\")\n\n# List files\nfiles = client.list_files(\"/tmp\")\nprint(files)\n\n# Clean up\nclient.stop()\n```\n\n### Using Context Manager\n\n```python\nfrom agentcube import CodeInterpreterClient\n\nwith CodeInterpreterClient(\n    name=\"my-interpreter\",\n    namespace=\"default\",\n    router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n) as client:\n    output = client.execute_command(\"ls -la\")\n    print(output)\n# Session is automatically cleaned up\n```\n\n### Agent Runtime\n\n```python\nfrom agentcube import AgentRuntimeClient\n\n# Create a client (session is automatically bootstrapped)\nclient = AgentRuntimeClient(\n    agent_name=\"my-agent\",\n    namespace=\"default\",\n    router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n)\n\n# Invoke the agent\nresponse = client.invoke({\n    \"input\": \"Hello, Agent!\",\n    \"context\": {\"user\": \"alice\"}\n})\nprint(response)\n\n# Clean up\nclient.close()\n```\n\n### Using Context Manager\n\n```python\nfrom agentcube import AgentRuntimeClient\n\nwith AgentRuntimeClient(\n    agent_name=\"my-agent\",\n    namespace=\"default\",\n    router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n) as client:\n    response = client.invoke({\"input\": \"Hello, Agent!\"})\n    print(response)\n# Session is automatically cleaned up\n```\n\n## Configuration\n\n### Environment Variables\n\n- `ROUTER_URL`: Default Router URL (can be overridden in constructor)\n- `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`: Default Workload Manager URL (for Code Interpreter control plane)\n\n### Authentication\n\nThe SDK supports Bearer token authentication:\n\n```python\n# Direct token\nclient = CodeInterpreterClient(\n    router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n    auth_token=\"my-token\"\n)\n\n# Kubernetes service account token (automatic)\nclient = CodeInterpreterClient(\n    router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n    # Token is automatically read from /var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token\n)\n```\n\n### Timeouts\n\nDefault timeouts:\n- Connect timeout: 5.0 seconds\n- Read timeout: 120 seconds\n\nCustom timeouts:\n\n```python\nfrom agentcube import AgentRuntimeClient\n\nclient = AgentRuntimeClient(\n    agent_name=\"my-agent\",\n    router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n    timeout=60,           # Read timeout in seconds\n    connect_timeout=2.0,  # Connect timeout in seconds\n)\n```\n\nPer-call timeout override:\n\n```python\n# Code Interpreter\noutput = client.execute_command(\"sleep 10\", timeout=30.0)\n\n# Agent Runtime\nresponse = client.invoke({\"input\": \"test\"}, timeout=60.0)\n```\n\n## Error Handling\n\n```python\nfrom agentcube import CodeInterpreterClient\nfrom agentcube.exceptions import CommandExecutionError\n\ntry:\n    client = CodeInterpreterClient(router_url=\"http://router:8080\")\n    output = client.execute_command(\"ls /invalid\")\nexcept CommandExecutionError as e:\n    print(f\"Command failed with exit code {e.exit_code}\")\n    print(f\"Error: {e.stderr}\")\nexcept ValueError as e:\n    print(f\"Configuration error: {e}\")\n```\n\n## API Reference\n\n### CodeInterpreterClient\n\n| Method | Description |\n|--------|-------------|\n| `execute_command(command, timeout)` | Execute a shell command |\n| `run_code(language, code, timeout)` | Run code in a specific language |\n| `write_file(content, remote_path)` | Write content to a remote file |\n| `upload_file(local_path, remote_path)` | Upload a local file |\n| `download_file(remote_path, local_path)` | Download a remote file |\n| `list_files(path)` | List files in a directory |\n| `stop()` | Stop the session and cleanup |\n\n### AgentRuntimeClient\n\n| Method | Description |\n|--------|-------------|\n| `invoke(payload, timeout)` | Invoke the agent with a payload |\n| `close()` | Close the HTTP session |\n\n## Development\n\n### Running Tests\n\n```bash\npytest tests/ -v\n```\n\n### Code Style\n\n```bash\nruff check agentcube/\nruff format agentcube/\n```\n\n### Type Checking\n\n```bash\nmypy agentcube/\n```\n\n## License\n\n[Specify your license here]","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/README.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<dia